AIM: 
To write a C program to solve a quadratic equation using the formula method from 
numerical methods. 
 
 
ALGORITHM: 
1. Start the program. 
2. Read the coefficients aaa, bbb, and ccc of the quadratic equation ax^2+bx+c=0 
3. Calculate the discriminant: 
      D =b^2-4ac
4. If D>0: Roots are real and distinct: 
     x1= (-b+√ D)/2a , x2= (-b-√ D)/2a
5. If D=0: Roots are real and equal: 
    x1 = x2 = -b/2a
6. If D<0: Roots are complex: 
    realpart = -b/2a, imgpart = √ -D/2a
7. Display the roots according to the discriminant value. 
8. Stop the program. 
 
 
PROGRAM:  
#include <stdio.h> 
#include <math.h> 
int main() { 
float a, b, c, discriminant, realPart, imagPart, root1, root2; 
printf("Enter coefficients a, b, and c: "); 
scanf("%f %f %f", &a, &b, &c); 
discriminant = b * b - 4 * a * c; 
if (discriminant > 0) { 
root1 = (-b + sqrt(discriminant)) / (2 * a); 
root2 = (-b - sqrt(discriminant)) / (2 * a); 
printf("Roots are real and distinct.\n"); 
printf("Root1 = %.2f, Root2 = %.2f\n", root1, root2); 
} 
else if (discriminant == 0) { 
root1 = root2 = -b / (2 * a); 
printf("Roots are real and equal.\n"); 
printf("Root1 = Root2 = %.2f\n", root1); 
} 
else { 
realPart = -b / (2 * a); 
imagPart = sqrt(-discriminant) / (2 * a); 
printf("Roots are complex and imaginary.\n"); 
printf("Root1 = %.2f + %.2fi, Root2 = %.2f - %.2fi\n", realPart, imagPart, realPart, 
imagPart); 
} 
return 0; 
} 
 
 
